Matter before the Court for Sentencing.  Hearing proceeded.  Presentence report previously reviewed by the parties.  The Court makes reference to the in chambers conference held off the record on today.  Statements made by MPD Detective Draeger, the state, Bishop Sedwick D., Keondre W., defense, and defendant.

COUNT 1:  The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 90 MONTHS with credit of 496 DAYS time served.  The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 30 MONTHS with Dodge to be the reception center.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 60 MONTHS.  

The defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.  

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs by the end of supervision period- any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment;
*Provided DNA sample- pay surcharge;
*Pay supervision fees;
*Provide a DNA sample - pay surcharge;
*Obtain high school diploma or GED or HSED;
*Obtain bachelors degree;
*Complete 150 hours of community service- organizations/locations to be determined by Bishop Sedwick D. or Detective Draeger;
*Obtain employment- hours as deemed appropriated by department of corrections;
*No Contact with any other non-blood family members under the age of 25 years if your brother is present;

The state is in compliance with victim rights legislation.  The Court ordered restitution payable in the stipulated amounts of $500.00 to Judy H. and $119.00 to Dewain R. to be paid by the end of supervision period.  Any remaining balance to convert to civil judgment.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.  Appeal rights given the Court. 
